The paper deals with a graph layout problem, which involves organizing the nodes and edges of a graph in a visually appealing way. This problem is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new exact approach to the problem, which involves formulating it as a quadratic assignment problem. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of optimization (cs.SI).
